------------------------------------------------------------ 
		 Spatial Data Integrator
------------------------------------------------------------ 
 * Community website : http://spatialdataintegrator.com
 * Wiki : http://www.talendforge.org/wiki/doku.php?id=sdi:MainPage
 * Forum : http://www.talendforge.org/forum/viewforum.php?id=9


------------------------------------------------------------ 
 Build SDI
--
In order to build SpatialDataIntegrator jar file run from the 
command line: 
ant


------------------------------------------------------------ 
 Install SDI into an existing TOS directory 
--
In order to install SpatialDataIntegrator (all components, librairies
and templates) in an existing Talend Open Studio installation: 
 * edit the sdi.properties file
 * change talend.dir and talend.cpt properties
 * then run from the command line:
ant install

This will copy all geospatial components into the TOS installation 
directory.



------------------------------------------------------------ 
 Create SDI package from an existing SDI installer 
--
In order to build a new SpatialDataIntegrator package including 
all components, librairies and templates download a previous 
SDI installer from spatialdataintegrator.com. Then: 
 * edit the sdi.properties file
 * change sdi.dir, sdi.file and sdi.cpt properties
 * then run from the command line:
ant packFromSDI



------------------------------------------------------------ 
 Demo geodata and workspace 
-- 
 * Demo data are available under the geodata directory.
 * Workspace used for unit testing is the workspace directory.


